{
  "texts": [
    "In this research, the same Informer structure as in the original paper [32] is applied.Temporal Fusion Transformer (TFT): TFT is built on a sequence-to-sequence architecture that uses LSTM layers to process time series data.",
    "What makes TFT innovative is its use of gated residual networks and variable selection networks, which help the model choose the most relevant inputs at each time step.",
    "It also includes a multi-head attention mechanism to focus on important past events, and it separates static, past, and future covariates to better handle complex time series.",
    "These design choices allow TFT to provide both strong performance and interpretability.",
    "In this study, TFT is implemented using the PyTorch Forecasting library, which supports hyperparameter tuning with Optuna and the integration of additional features such as sentiment scores, making it well suited for our multi-source financial data."
  ]
}